; Regression test for issue #1114: cost balance check silently accepted
; unbalanced transactions when the cost commodity's display precision was 0.
;
; Cost amounts after @ are parsed with PARSE_NO_MIGRATE, so their precision
; is not propagated to the commodity.  When the cost commodity has no other
; amounts establishing a display precision, is_zero() would render sub-unit
; remainders (e.g., 0.22 EUR) as "0" at precision 0 and falsely treat the
; transaction as balanced.
;
; This transaction is unbalanced: 200/9 = 22.222... EUR, not 22 EUR.
; Before the fix, it was silently accepted.

2015/01/01 Unbalanced fractional cost
    Expenses:Food   (1/9 FOO) @ 200 EUR
    Assets:Cash     -22 EUR

test bal -> 1
__ERROR__
While parsing file "$FILE", line 15:
While balancing transaction from "$FILE", lines 13-15:
> 2015/01/01 Unbalanced fractional cost
>     Expenses:Food   (1/9 FOO) @ 200 EUR
>     Assets:Cash     -22 EUR
Unbalanced remainder is:
                   0
Amount to balance against:
       22.222222 EUR
Error: Transaction does not balance
end test
